parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the power steering system can cause the steering wheel to lock or become difficult to turn, making it hard to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The steering wheel feels stiff or hard to turn
the power steering pump makes a loud noise
the steering fluid leaks
the vehicle makes a grinding or shuttering noise when turning
the steering wheel seizes or locks up.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the clutch master cylinder can cause the clutch pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The clutch pedal feels soft or spongy
the clutch pedal sticks to the floor
the clutch pedal does not return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the clutch pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to shift into gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air conditioning system can cause discomfort and distraction while driving, which can lead to accidents.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Incomplete recalls can lead to continued safety risks for vehicle owners, as the necessary repairs may not be made to address the underlying issues.
